Hi Keryn, 

The original platform was setup to only handle 1 stripe account as this is normal practice. Stripe also only allows 1 bank account to be setup in their portal to send the funds to. In most situations like this, an inter-company invoice/transfer is the best option. You could have a bank account that all payments are send to and then periodically sent onto the respective businesses.

So the only real solution would be to have 2 duplicate websites, one for ADL and one for MEL. I'm happy to chat about this, if more explanation is needed.

Ok great thanks Heath, we'll have a play and let you know if there is anything else.

Were you able to determine whether using 2 stripe accounts was going to be better than displaying the 2 bank account details, I'm not sure how this will work through stripe?

Thanks.

Keryn Rogers

Hi Keryn, 

Here is an update on our progress. Everything has been completed, except the "Add another field for Admin charge not shown to client". This is going to take a little more work as it affects quite a few of the calculations. In the short-term, you can add a negative value in the "Hidden Discount" field to achieve the same outcome. 

Completed Items:

When creating a quote proposal

  • Final page standard hire period needs to be 5 weeks not 4 and no free weeks
    ***We have defaulted this to 5 weeks
  • Final page rental bond not standard when occupied property but still an option. 
    ***We have defaulted this to $0
  • ADVANTAGE PLUS can we take this out for now.  I’ll talk to you about where we can add a link to our payment plan option.
    ***Done
Edits for Proposal Link:

  • PHONE NUMER-Top of screen needs to both Adelaide and Melbourne DFS
    ***Done
  • Remove all references to Advantage Styling on online proposal page and through out the quote platform and replace with Dressed for Sale
    ***Done
  • EFT SELECTED AS PAYMENT OPTION - Change to all DFS details 2 bank accounts 
    ***Done
  • THANK YOU FOR YOUR BOOKING WITH ADVANTAGE STYLING
    ***Done
